And the last time you stayed here,

31:23.883 --> 31:26.553
-it was your... Please just listen to me.
-I know... No, don't...

31:26.594 --> 31:28.394
It was your sister who found your blood.

31:28.430 --> 31:31.730
Okay, I am aware of that.
It's not going to happen ever again.

31:31.766 --> 31:34.226
You don't understand, Dad.
If you don't let me stay here...

31:34.352 --> 31:35.732
-No, I do understand.
-...I have nowhere else to go.

31:36.021 --> 31:38.441
Five minutes.
Thank you, thank you very much.

31:38.565 --> 31:39.565
-David?
-Yes?

31:39.607 --> 31:41.607
-Can she stay with you?
-No, she can't.

31:41.693 --> 31:43.153
I can't let it happen to your sister
and I can't...

31:43.236 --> 31:45.906
Dad, you can't! You have to let me stay here.

31:46.114 --> 31:48.414
-Please.
-No. She's your friend, mate.

31:48.450 --> 31:49.740
But you just stood up in church and said

31:49.784 --> 31:51.454
how important it is for people
to have strong support.

31:51.536 --> 31:54.036
I know what I just did and I am having
a tough time at the moment, Dylan.

31:54.080 --> 31:55.750
-I've got a lot on my...
-Please. I know. So is she!

31:55.915 --> 31:57.535
-You love me so much?
-I would do anything for you, but...

31:57.625 --> 31:59.625
You don't want me to sleep in my room
so I can get better?

31:59.711 --> 32:01.171
-Dylan, please.
-...go home to something like this.

32:01.212 --> 32:02.842
-Can I just have five seconds to try...
-She trusts you.

32:02.881 --> 32:05.551
-And you have a huge house.
-You have a huge house?

32:05.717 --> 32:07.887
-Well, it's big!
-Fine!

32:09.554 --> 32:11.644
You shut up, and you stop sulking,

32:11.723 --> 32:14.183
and you're all staying at my place.

32:14.351 --> 32:15.481
...one of the things I can't do...

32:15.560 --> 32:16.640
You would not do anything

32:16.728 --> 32:18.478
because you're not letting me sleep
where I need to sleep!

32:18.563 --> 32:19.613
Mr. Yohe, my name's David McKenna.

32:19.689 --> 32:22.399
Do you mind if Renee stays with me
for a couple of days?

32:24.319 --> 32:25.699
She's gonna need to get some things.

32:54.974 --> 32:56.394
Lovely.

33:04.275 --> 33:06.735
You moving out or you moving in?

33:06.778 --> 33:07.948
Not sure yet.

33:08.029 --> 33:09.069
This is fancy.

33:10.907 --> 33:12.367
-Hey, Renee.
-Yep.

33:13.201 --> 33:17.411
In this house
there's no booze and no drugs. Okay?

33:17.497 --> 33:20.537
Just sleep, coffee and cigarettes.

33:20.583 --> 33:22.713
My number one rule, we don't get tired
and we don't get hungry.

33:25.046 --> 33:26.046
Okay.

33:26.131 --> 33:27.971
-You in?
-I'm in.

33:28.216 --> 33:29.716
Let's do it.

33:31.261 --> 33:35.221
Okay, kitchen, my quarters, hot tub,
you lot can park it upstairs,

33:35.306 --> 33:37.596
middle room's my office, no kids allowed.
We clear?

33:37.684 --> 33:40.444
And you got first dibs. You two...

33:47.652 --> 33:50.362
Addiction is a very complicated relationship.

33:50.572 --> 33:52.572
We've been friends with Renee
for, like, 12 years.

33:52.657 --> 33:54.657
-Trust me, we know.
-Okay, all right.

33:54.743 --> 33:56.083
This is not Renee.

33:57.245 --> 34:00.575
<i>You have to thinkInvasion of
the Body Snatchersor something, okay?</i>

34:01.583 --> 34:04.673
Every single thing in her,
every fiber of her being

34:04.711 --> 34:07.011
wants one thing, is thinking about one thing,

34:07.047 --> 34:09.917
cares about one thing and it's not you,
and it's not me.

34:10.257 --> 34:12.047
It's drugs, okay?

34:12.344 --> 34:13.853
So what do we do?

34:13.887 --> 34:15.137
What we do is...

34:15.221 --> 34:19.271
Okay, the game plan is distractions,
distractions, distractions. Okay?

34:19.351 --> 34:21.900
Dylan, you're on snack duty, okay?

34:21.936 --> 34:24.856
Take Renee, don't let her out of your sight.
Come straight back.

34:24.938 --> 34:27.529
She'll ask you to go someplace else,
you don't go, you don't deviate,

34:27.567 --> 34:29.937
you come back here.
Half an hour, 30 minutes. All right?

34:30.027 --> 34:32.277
Or I'm coming after you. Jessie?

34:33.031 --> 34:35.741
Jessie, take all the knives and anything
sharp in the house and hide them.

34:36.076 --> 34:37.735
You want me to
hide all the knives in the house?

34:38.036 --> 34:39.746
Did you see her arm?

34:41.331 --> 34:44.041
Look, all the ways you want to punish Renee
for being a shit friend

34:44.208 --> 34:46.248
will pale in comparison to the ways
Renee will punish herself.

34:46.335 --> 34:48.246
Now get on with it.

34:49.047 --> 34:50.877
All right, let's go.

34:51.091 --> 34:54.051
Dylan? Don't forget my Lucky Charms.

34:59.683 --> 35:02.733
Animal crackers! Oh, yes!

35:05.522 --> 35:07.072
I missed you.

35:07.524 --> 35:10.364
Yeah, I mean, why did we stop hanging out
in the first place?

35:10.485 --> 35:13.655
What is this? What are we doing?
We're hanging out.

35:13.738 --> 35:15.368
We used to hang out, like, every day together

35:15.407 --> 35:17.867
and now you're a completely different person

35:17.909 --> 35:20.079
doing different things and I don't know...

35:20.161 --> 35:22.291
Different things?

35:23.164 --> 35:24.424
You know what I'm talking about.

35:24.541 --> 35:26.381
-I know what you're talking about.
-You know.

35:26.710 --> 35:28.960
Why did you do that to your arm?

35:31.381 --> 35:33.431
It just looked right.

35:33.508 --> 35:37.428
Well, I like the way you look without it.
'Cause it's not true.

35:37.762 --> 35:39.062
Crap, sorry. I didn't know this was...

35:39.764 --> 35:42.314
No, no, no. I got this. I got this.

35:42.475 --> 35:44.055
Okay.

37:37.799 --> 37:39.929
Whoa, McKenna, whoa!

37:40.010 --> 37:41.550
Jamie!

37:42.554 --> 37:44.564
You nearly gave me a heart attack,
you wanker.

37:44.639 --> 37:46.099
When did we start sounding the alarm?

37:46.725 --> 37:47.725
Today.

37:47.767 --> 37:48.807
And when did we get new friends?

37:49.269 --> 37:50.269
Keeping her safe.

37:51.896 --> 37:53.566
-Obvious enough.
-Renee,

37:53.648 --> 37:57.148
meet Jamie, my sometimes housemate,
who I'm guessing missed his flight.

37:57.402 --> 37:58.572
Jessie. Good night.

37:58.945 --> 38:01.065
Dylan took your room,
so you can bunk with him.

38:01.573 --> 38:04.663
All right! Bunk buddies. See you up there.

38:04.743 --> 38:08.083
This is David McKenna.
Everything's fine, false alarm.

38:12.083 --> 38:14.673
Want some Lucky Charms?

38:19.215 --> 38:24.045
I know this isn't any of my business,
but you all right, Renee?

38:24.137 --> 38:26.507
I'm a coozer.

38:26.765 --> 38:30.185
-A coozer?
-It's coke and booze together.

38:30.226 --> 38:32.596
I made it up, do you like it?

38:34.689 --> 38:37.899
Yeah. I don't think McKenna coozes much.

38:38.234 --> 38:39.904
He's such a quitter.

38:40.945 --> 38:43.565
So what's you're... Who do you...
What's your deal?

38:45.116 --> 38:47.616
I'm actually a lot more
interested in you right now.

38:47.702 --> 38:48.752
I'll bet.

38:51.748 --> 38:55.418
I need a place to detox for a few days
till I go to rehab

38:55.502 --> 38:59.592
and McKenna is donating to my charity.

39:00.632 --> 39:02.472
Nosy.

39:02.717 --> 39:05.097
I didn't mean to be nosy.

39:05.553 --> 39:07.643
I'm just really...

39:08.848 --> 39:10.138
That's really brave.

39:10.725 --> 39:12.385
I'm happy for you.

39:15.105 --> 39:16.725
Why doesn't he have knives?

39:20.568 --> 39:21.568
So what do you do?

39:22.904 --> 39:26.914
I am a rep for a surf company.

39:27.283 --> 39:31.253
McKenna's nice enough to let me crash here
when I'm in town.

39:31.663 --> 39:33.583
-You're like a traveling salesman?
-Yeah.

39:34.082 --> 39:35.712
Legit job.

39:35.792 --> 39:38.592
Office. Grown-up stuff.

39:39.212 --> 39:42.012
But what I really wanna do is write.

39:44.843 --> 39:46.763
You like Paper Route?

39:46.845 --> 39:48.845
They're playing at
the Florida Music Fest tomorrow.

39:49.597 --> 39:51.677
Yeah. We should go.
You think the warden will let you out?

39:51.891 --> 39:54.061
I will dig my way out.

39:54.894 --> 39:56.484
Right on.

39:57.939 --> 39:59.979
So you out tomorrow morning or...

40:00.358 --> 40:02.568
Actually the day after, if that's okay with you.

40:02.652 --> 40:04.242
Yeah, the more the merrier.

40:04.404 --> 40:07.034
All right, thank you.

40:07.157 --> 40:08.947
No problem.

40:10.452 --> 40:12.332
Appreciate it.

40:13.705 --> 40:16.705
And congratulations on your new life, Renee.

40:18.043 --> 40:20.213
-Good night.
-Bye!

40:24.549 --> 40:26.759
Pretty good.

40:28.345 --> 40:29.595
How are you feeling?

40:30.055 --> 40:31.845
Like my soul got kicked in the nuts.

40:33.266 --> 40:34.476
Good.

40:34.684 --> 40:39.064
Well, not good that you feel
like your soul's been kicked in the balls,

40:39.439 --> 40:42.779
but it's good you're being honest.
Secrets make you sick.

40:43.735 --> 40:45.065
I like that, McKenna.

40:45.195 --> 40:47.355
-Remember it.
-Yes, sir.

40:51.076 --> 40:52.656
Thank you

40:53.745 --> 40:55.365
for all of this.

40:56.748 --> 40:58.748
Somebody did it for me,
you'll do it for someone else.

41:00.085 --> 41:02.545
All right, thanks for the sandwich.

41:03.213 --> 41:04.803
Sleep tight.

41:21.314 --> 41:22.774
This is slave labor.

41:22.982 --> 41:24.942
I prefer the term internship.

41:25.068 --> 41:26.778
It's all gonna be back next week.

41:27.153 --> 41:29.413
So will you. It's a test of wills, mate.

41:30.407 --> 41:32.117
-Hey.
-There she is!

41:32.367 --> 41:34.367
You all right, sleeping beauty?

41:38.248 --> 41:41.328
You have an extra one of those... Thank you.

41:42.627 --> 41:44.127
Hey, boss?

41:44.295 --> 41:47.215
I have three...
No, I have four questions for you.

41:47.382 --> 41:50.222
-I'll answer two. Maybe.
-Okay.

41:50.343 --> 41:52.103
One, why don't you have any furniture?

41:52.178 --> 41:53.718
Two, where'd you get your tattoo,

41:53.847 --> 41:58.597
three, how come you left England,
and four, I'll ask you later.

41:58.727 --> 42:00.397
One, I just haven't found the right sofa yet,

42:00.437 --> 42:03.607
I wish people would stop pressuring me,
and two, I got that bad boy in prison.

42:03.732 --> 42:05.282
Prison? What did you do?

42:05.400 --> 42:07.740
Only answering two questions.

42:08.069 --> 42:11.069
-Hey! Right on.
-Hey, Jamie!

42:11.156 --> 42:12.236
Looking great, guys.

42:12.532 --> 42:14.992
So what are you doing
your last night in Orlando?

42:15.076 --> 42:17.496
I was thinking Florida Music Fest.

42:18.538 --> 42:20.748
I mean, your band's playing, right?
We'll all go together.

42:21.041 --> 42:24.211
You have bands? McKenna, I wanna go.

42:24.502 --> 42:27.212
One band, and, no, you can't go,
you're staying with the babysitters.

42:27.964 --> 42:29.424
I thought she needed distractions.

42:29.507 --> 42:32.507
Yeah, if there's music,
I'm not thinking about drugs.

42:32.635 --> 42:35.635
No, there's no drugs at a music festival.
It's a great idea.

42:36.014 --> 42:38.564
Exactly. I don't have extra tickets anyway,
so it's settled.

42:38.725 --> 42:39.845
Turns out Hurley's sponsoring the event.

42:39.893 --> 42:43.523
Made a call, got us VIP treatment
and Paper Route's playing.

42:45.023 --> 42:47.733
And we'll be there
to support your band, Between the Trees.

42:47.901 --> 42:48.941
Why thank you, Jamie.

42:49.277 --> 42:54.987
<i>What would you say if I told you
that I'm not giving up?</i>

42:55.075 --> 42:58.235
<i>However long it takes</i>

43:00.747 --> 43:03.497
<i>It's clear that things have changed</i>

43:03.541 --> 43:05.381
<i>Since when we started</i>

43:05.418 --> 43:08.918
<i>But we can't just walk away, babe</i>

43:09.005 --> 43:11.755
<i>So I am telling you that</i>

43:11.841 --> 43:18.221
<i>I know things aren't quite
like what they used to be</i>

43:20.392 --> 43:22.272
<i>Different faces,
different places</i>

43:22.394 --> 43:26.114
I needed this. Thank you.

43:28.233 --> 43:29.733
You're welcome.

43:32.362 --> 43:35.492
Boys, nice one, well done, more of
the same please. That was the bollocks.

43:35.824 --> 43:37.204
So when are we gonna meet Stevo?

43:37.242 --> 43:39.452
Just let me handle the business.

43:39.536 --> 43:41.406
You're going to meet him
right after the second set.

43:41.496 --> 43:43.326
Go make daddy proud.

43:45.917 --> 43:50.837
<i>Where have I landed
I don't quite remember</i>

43:50.880 --> 43:56.050
<i>I fell to pieces
one night in December</i>

43:56.136 --> 43:59.556
<i>The memories of losing you</i>

43:59.597 --> 44:02.057
<i>You're like a ghost</i>

44:02.100 --> 44:05.650
<i>Tracing where I said to you</i>

44:05.729 --> 44:08.309
<i>I wish you would listen</i>

44:08.398 --> 44:10.478
-Lift me up!
-Oh, no!

44:10.567 --> 44:14.397
Yes, Dylan, lift me up! Lift me up! Come on!

44:14.529 --> 44:17.069
Please, you guys, if anyone
is doing drugs up there,

44:17.157 --> 44:18.737
I will come right down immediately.

44:19.075 --> 44:20.445
They might be.

44:20.577 --> 44:22.577
No, no, no. McKenna will kill me.

44:22.704 --> 44:24.714
-Please, please, Dylan.
-Just watch from right here.

44:24.831 --> 44:26.831
Come on, one...

44:27.459 --> 44:28.959
Be right back?

44:29.044 --> 44:32.384
Girl scout's honor. One, two, three!

44:33.548 --> 44:38.508
<i>Looking for love like
a bride looks for dresses</i>

44:38.553 --> 44:41.933
<i>The memories of losing you</i>

44:42.015 --> 44:44.425
<i>You're like a ghost</i>

44:44.517 --> 44:47.807
<i>Tracing where I said to you</i>

44:47.896 --> 44:50.646
<i>I wish you would listen</i>

44:50.732 --> 44:53.282
<i>I wish you would listen</i>

44:53.360 --> 44:55.860
<i>I wish you would listen</i>

44:55.904 --> 44:57.704
<i>To get through it</i>

44:58.323 --> 45:00.663
<i>I wish you would listen</i>

45:00.867 --> 45:01.987
McKenna?

45:02.077 --> 45:03.447
-Stevo.
-What's up?

45:03.536 --> 45:04.576
-How you doing?
-Good.

45:04.662 --> 45:05.872
-Safe trip?
-All good.

45:05.914 --> 45:09.384
Okay, good. Anyway, listen,
are you a Between the Trees fan yet?

45:10.251 --> 45:12.881
-We'll see.
-Okay.

45:12.921 --> 45:14.051
When can I meet the band?

45:14.130 --> 45:17.840
I'll introduce you right after the second set.
Listen, would you excuse me a minute, yeah?

45:18.510 --> 45:20.010
Hey, where's Renee?

45:20.053 --> 45:21.053
She's up there, we just put her up there.

45:21.513 --> 45:25.933
Tell me you are joking. You put her up there?
We're at a music festival!

45:26.101 --> 45:28.141
It's fine, McKenna!

45:28.645 --> 45:30.055
Well, she's not there now!

45:30.146 --> 45:32.146
I told you this was a bad idea!

45:32.232 --> 45:35.072
Okay, Jessie, you go that way,
you get back in the crowd

45:35.110 --> 45:37.490
and you come with me!

45:47.455 --> 45:50.035
-Yohe! Yohe!
-Hey!

45:50.750 --> 45:53.460
Where you been?
What happened to you back in Daytona?

45:53.545 --> 45:55.205
What, you get saved or kidnapped
or something?

45:55.296 --> 45:58.296
A little bit of both.
I lost my group I came with.

45:58.758 --> 46:02.758
Why don't you get in,
I'll take you around the front by the stage.

46:08.768 --> 46:12.648
Hey, wanna go downtown?
I got some mad snow not far from here.

46:12.731 --> 46:15.191
No, no more snow. I'm done with that.

46:15.275 --> 46:18.355
Two days sober, man, three days to rehab.

46:18.445 --> 46:19.855
How Hollywood of you.

46:19.904 --> 46:21.994
Come on, you sure you don't want to go out
with a bang?

46:22.073 --> 46:23.703
No. Take me back.

46:24.034 --> 46:25.374
All right.

46:28.830 --> 46:31.880
-Renee!
-Hey, hey, hold on.

46:32.500 --> 46:36.090
Hey, all right. Thanks.

46:36.212 --> 46:37.882
Sure thing. Stay safe.

46:38.006 --> 46:40.296
Yeah, you too. Hey.

46:41.343 --> 46:43.393
Is that one of your boyfriends?

46:43.553 --> 46:45.813
What's your problem? No, no.
What's your problem?

46:45.889 --> 46:48.179
Did you just go use with that guy?

46:48.224 --> 46:50.484
-Did I just use with that guy?
-Did you just go use with that guy?

46:50.560 --> 46:52.900
No, I didn't go use with that guy, Jess!

46:52.937 --> 46:55.607
Just go home, dude, if you don't want
to be here, you don't have to be here.

46:55.690 --> 46:56.780
I'm sure you'd love that, wouldn't you,

46:56.858 --> 46:58.648
so you could have a house full of men
all to yourself, right?

46:58.735 --> 47:01.195
What are you talking about?

47:01.363 --> 47:03.283
We used to be a family.

47:03.365 --> 47:05.905
-Do you know how much that means to me?
-Yes.

47:05.950 --> 47:10.370
You gave up everything for some prick
at a bullshit rave.

47:10.413 --> 47:13.883
Whoa, you don't know
what happened with Sean. Okay?

47:13.917 --> 47:16.037
I don't care what happened, Renee,
'cause it's not about Sean,

47:16.127 --> 47:19.547
it's about you giving up everything
for the slightest bit of attention.

47:19.673 --> 47:20.843
Listen to me right now.

47:20.882 --> 47:23.842
I will tell you everything right now. He...

47:23.927 --> 47:25.257
Stop right there. Just stop right there.

47:25.345 --> 47:26.805
I don't care and I don't want to hear it.

47:26.888 --> 47:30.808
I'm so sick of
hearing your stories and your sadness

47:30.892 --> 47:33.982
and seeing your pity scars
all over your body.

47:34.062 --> 47:37.072
I'm so sick of it. I'm done.

47:37.148 --> 47:38.898
<i>I want to see what I dream</i>

47:38.983 --> 47:41.283
<i>I want the inconvenience</i>

47:41.361 --> 47:46.531
<i>I hope you see that
when you fall in love...</i>

48:10.724 --> 48:14.194
Stevo, no, no, Stevo's fine, yeah, yeah, yeah,
he loved it.

48:14.269 --> 48:16.559
Yeah, he really did, yeah.

48:16.646 --> 48:19.726
Yeah, something came up.

48:19.774 --> 48:23.574
Just let me deal with the contracts, all right?

48:23.611 --> 48:27.951
No, no, no, no, I'll be there. Yeah.
No, I wouldn't miss it for the world.

48:28.658 --> 48:29.658
Yeah, okay.

48:46.801 --> 48:49.261
You going out for a smoke?

48:54.017 --> 48:56.057
Don't you have a plane to catch?

48:56.519 --> 49:00.149
It's delayed till we get you to rehab.

49:01.358 --> 49:06.648
When I was a little kid I used to say that
planes were like these big friendly giants

49:07.405 --> 49:12.825
and if I had, like, a bad dream, bad idea,

49:13.078 --> 49:17.538
a plane would just fly them away.

49:18.124 --> 49:19.714
Sounds beautiful.

49:23.755 --> 49:25.965
Just wanna escape all this shit.

49:29.219 --> 49:32.429
Yeah, you know, you remind me
of my friend, Zeke.

49:33.098 --> 49:34.218
Zeke.

49:34.307 --> 49:37.017
He'd say the worst part of his day
was the paddling back to shore.

49:37.435 --> 49:39.805
-Surfing?
-Yeah. He was a surf buddy.

49:43.191 --> 49:44.441
He died two months ago.

49:45.360 --> 49:51.200
Took his own life. Now, I don't know
if I could have said something.

49:52.409 --> 49:56.369
But I wanna be the guy
who can say the right thing.

49:56.413 --> 49:58.043
You know?

50:01.042 --> 50:03.842
I think people might need more than words.

50:05.547 --> 50:06.627
Maybe.

50:11.886 --> 50:17.016
-You all right?
-Yeah, I think I... I think.

50:18.810 --> 50:21.400
Is she okay? Is she all right?

50:23.189 --> 50:24.819
-No.
-Need some water?

50:25.150 --> 50:27.190
-A blanket?
-She needs a bed.

50:28.403 --> 50:31.243
Here's a bucket, in case you need to...

50:31.322 --> 50:34.662
-I'm so cold.
-It's all right, I got it.

50:36.953 --> 50:41.213
My dad put this by my bed
every time I was ill.

50:41.249 --> 50:42.499
Let me get you some water.

50:45.837 --> 50:47.587
Is this normal?

50:48.089 --> 50:49.669
This is the worst part.

50:50.508 --> 50:52.138
Great.

50:52.218 --> 50:53.678
I'll be next door, okay?

50:54.971 --> 50:57.271
Yeah, hang in there.

51:24.250 --> 51:25.460
I missed you.

51:29.422 --> 51:30.722
You wanna go for a ride?

51:31.841 --> 51:33.471
No.

51:51.277 --> 51:52.607
Am I ever going to be okay?

51:56.574 --> 51:59.414
Why did you make me like this?

52:14.801 --> 52:16.471
No, ma'am. What are you thinking...

52:18.930 --> 52:21.470
<i>She's hurting herself. She's cutting herself,</i>

52:21.558 --> 52:24.228
<i>and I don't understand.
What is wrong with her?</i>

52:25.228 --> 52:28.768
<i>Those pills are nothing. I don't want her...
I don't want her taking all those pills,</i>

52:28.857 --> 52:30.357
<i>do you understand?</i>

52:31.401 --> 52:32.861
<i>Why does she keep doing these things?</i>

52:32.902 --> 52:35.782
<i>It doesn't help to ask why.</i>

52:36.489 --> 52:40.619
<i>Why can't we help it? Why is she doing
these things? She's hurting herself.</i>

53:55.694 --> 53:57.364
What did I say?

53:57.404 --> 54:02.124
All business comes and goes through me.

54:02.200 --> 54:05.250
No, that's... No, I...

54:05.328 --> 54:08.158
No, you... No, you...

54:08.248 --> 54:11.128
Will you let me speak? Please?

54:11.334 --> 54:13.884
You really wanna have this conversation?

54:14.004 --> 54:19.724
Three months ago you were performing
for a bunch of drunks in a bloody toilet.

54:20.635 --> 54:22.255
Don't you ever speak to me like that!

54:26.266 --> 54:27.386
Shit!

54:40.739 --> 54:41.909
Patio.

54:56.713 --> 54:58.343
It's nice, huh?

55:07.932 --> 55:10.812
-Bombay Bitches.
-What?

55:10.935 --> 55:13.895
Your third question.
The reason I left England.

55:13.980 --> 55:17.570
For a band.
I got stuck here in Orlando for a few more.

55:17.692 --> 55:19.572
Bombay Bitches.

55:24.115 --> 55:27.155
Yeah, yeah, all right, I do know it,
you can stop, thank you.

55:28.119 --> 55:31.709
They were also the reason
I hit rock bottom fairly predictably.

55:31.873 --> 55:36.673
So is that how you did it?
You started over somewhere new and...

55:37.212 --> 55:40.472
No. That didn't work for me.

55:41.341 --> 55:43.431
The problem was always me.

55:43.510 --> 55:47.010
Wherever I went, there I was.

55:48.723 --> 55:51.233
A friend once said to me
that I should never be left unattended

55:51.309 --> 55:53.519
because what I get back to is me.

55:54.688 --> 55:56.688
And me is the problem.

55:57.982 --> 55:59.032
You need other people.

56:01.945 --> 56:04.105
What's today's date?

56:04.989 --> 56:06.619
The 15th.

56:06.825 --> 56:08.865
-I have to go somewhere. Please.
-Not a chance.

56:08.910 --> 56:14.000
Please, please. I'll take Dylan. It'll be fine.
Please. It's important.

56:14.541 --> 56:17.171
Take Dylan. One hour.
I'm trusting you, all right?

56:17.210 --> 56:18.710
Thank you.

56:31.558 --> 56:34.308
Your dad said you were here.

56:36.938 --> 56:38.398
I'm really sorry we forgot.

56:43.737 --> 56:45.237
I miss you.

56:48.575 --> 56:49.735
It was like you died too, you know.

56:52.912 --> 56:54.212
I didn't.

56:54.748 --> 56:58.538
I miss her so much and I can't lose you, too.

57:06.384 --> 57:08.894
Why did you stop calling us?

57:09.554 --> 57:11.434
It was just overnight,
you just stopped calling us.

57:15.643 --> 57:17.193
I just...

57:18.229 --> 57:22.729
Something happened
and I just didn't want to talk about it.

57:23.443 --> 57:28.913
I wanted to be alone and it just got...
It got out of hand.

57:29.032 --> 57:31.282
What are you talking about?

57:31.409 --> 57:33.119
Halloween party.

57:33.703 --> 57:39.213
Sean pulled over in a parking lot
so I could throw up.

57:51.971 --> 57:53.471
<i>And he raped me.</i>

58:00.689 --> 58:02.149
I mean, we had no idea.

58:02.732 --> 58:04.482
I'm so sorry.

58:04.693 --> 58:07.243
I'm sorry. I'm so sorry.

58:08.613 --> 58:13.163
I'm sorry about everything I said at
the concert. I'm sorry about everything.

58:13.368 --> 58:15.038
I'm sorry.

58:16.037 --> 58:17.787
Will you please come back to McKenna's?

58:17.872 --> 58:21.172
I'll come back. I promise.

59:28.568 --> 59:30.148
All right, everyone, pay attention.

59:30.236 --> 59:33.406
She is never alone. Got it?

59:33.448 --> 59:35.908
And no crowd surfing
in the record shop, please,

59:35.992 --> 59:38.202
thank you very much, if you don't mind.

59:38.745 --> 59:39.945
Daja Grace.

59:40.038 --> 59:42.868
-I think it's Dasia, isn't it?
-Man.

59:42.999 --> 59:44.329
-What?
-Look.

59:44.376 --> 59:46.796
-You don't need that.
-I know.

59:46.878 --> 59:52.378
It's just the idea of eternal sobriety
scares me very much.

59:52.717 --> 59:54.047
-One day at a time.
-Right.

59:54.094 --> 59:55.144
Yeah.

59:55.220 --> 59:58.470
At least that's what my mom said
right before she relapsed.

59:59.057 --> 01:00:00.677
Good.

01:00:05.730 --> 01:00:07.070
Now that is impressive.

01:00:07.691 --> 01:00:09.571
-Coffee?
-Thank you.

01:00:09.943 --> 01:00:11.363
-That's cool.
-Yeah.

01:00:11.403 --> 01:00:15.573
The metalmark is the most beautiful butterfly.

01:00:15.615 --> 01:00:18.985
And it's the most fragile,
as it only lives a week.

01:00:20.745 --> 01:00:22.405
Isn't that sad?

01:00:24.082 --> 01:00:25.332
I wanted to ask you something.

01:00:25.375 --> 01:00:28.835
-Yeah?
-Don't get angry. It's kind of crazy.

01:00:28.878 --> 01:00:31.208
I love crazy. I'm insane.

01:00:33.216 --> 01:00:36.546
I want to write. I want to tell your story.

01:00:37.679 --> 01:00:40.889
-You want to write my story?
-Yeah, I do.

01:00:41.891 --> 01:00:47.401
It's powerful and because nobody says...

01:00:48.523 --> 01:00:51.743
Nobody talks about all the things
that happen to you.

01:00:51.901 --> 01:00:52.941
-You know?
-I know.

01:00:53.028 --> 01:00:55.318
And I just... I think it will help somebody.

01:00:57.782 --> 01:00:59.242
-Oh, God.
-You think it'll help...

01:00:59.325 --> 01:01:00.785
-I'm sorry, I'm sorry, I'm sorry.
-No, no, no, no, no!

01:01:00.869 --> 01:01:05.289
Jamie, I'm just...
You think it could help people, like...

01:01:06.708 --> 01:01:08.038
Yeah, I do.

01:01:10.170 --> 01:01:12.510
Okay, then do it. Sure.

01:01:12.547 --> 01:01:15.217
<i>Thanks for coming out to open mic night.</i>

01:01:15.300 --> 01:01:19.300
<i>-First up is Dylan Landers. Dylan?
-What?</i>

01:01:20.972 --> 01:01:23.432
Shit! Did you hear that?

01:01:23.516 --> 01:01:25.766
Get your stuff. We're going to the front.

01:01:27.354 --> 01:01:29.314
Hello.

01:01:29.397 --> 01:01:31.567
<i>My name is Dylan.</i>

01:01:31.608 --> 01:01:33.148
<i>Sorry.</i>

01:01:33.568 --> 01:01:34.818
<i>So this is a...</i>

01:01:34.903 --> 01:01:38.323
<i>I've never really done this before.
This is my first time.</i>

01:01:38.406 --> 01:01:41.906
<i>So today, tomorrow, actually,</i>

01:01:41.951 --> 01:01:47.001
<i>my best friend, Renee, is going to rehab.
For drugs. And...</i>

01:01:47.082 --> 01:01:49.462
<i>Not, like, to get drugs, but...
'Cause they don't...</i>

01:01:49.542 --> 01:01:50.882
<i>I don't think they have drugs there.</i>

01:01:50.960 --> 01:01:53.380
<i>So I want to sing a song for her.</i>

01:01:53.421 --> 01:01:55.421
<i>It's sort of like...</i>

01:01:55.507 --> 01:01:58.177
<i>It's kind of like a prayer in reverse.</i>

01:01:58.218 --> 01:02:00.548
<i>No, it's like, it's good. Here it goes.</i>

01:02:08.061 --> 01:02:13.861
<i>Come up to meet you
Tell you I'm sorry</i>

01:02:13.900 --> 01:02:19.950
<i>You don't know how lovely you are</i>

01:02:20.031 --> 01:02:25.951
<i>I had to find you
Tell you I need you</i>

01:02:26.037 --> 01:02:31.127
<i>Tell you I set you apart</i>

01:02:31.835 --> 01:02:37.375
<i>Tell me your secrets
Ask me your questions</i>

01:02:37.841 --> 01:02:42.471
<i>Oh, let's go back to the start</i>

01:02:43.263 --> 01:02:48.233
<i>Nobody said it was easy</i>

01:02:49.394 --> 01:02:53.654
<i>It's such a shame for us to part</i>

01:02:54.649 --> 01:02:59.989
<i>Nobody said it was easy</i>

01:03:00.739 --> 01:03:06.579
<i>No one ever said
It would be this hard</i>

01:03:08.747 --> 01:03:12.707
<i>I'm going back to the start</i>

01:03:27.265 --> 01:03:29.135
-Hey.
-Hey, hey, hey.

01:03:29.225 --> 01:03:30.345
That was a fun day, right?

01:03:30.393 --> 01:03:32.903
Yeah, fun, fun.

01:03:35.482 --> 01:03:37.322
Flying out?

01:03:37.400 --> 01:03:41.030
Yeah, I'm taking
the big friendly giant tomorrow.

01:03:41.071 --> 01:03:42.951
No, don't steal my line.

01:03:46.910 --> 01:03:51.370
I have a little... I have a little...
I just wanna give you something.

01:03:51.414 --> 01:03:53.964
-But it's weird.
-All right.

01:03:54.042 --> 01:03:56.382
Okay. Ready?

01:03:57.545 --> 01:03:59.705
Here, hold it like...

01:04:00.548 --> 01:04:01.878
Okay.

01:04:03.218 --> 01:04:07.638
I don't trust myself with it and I...

01:04:07.722 --> 01:04:10.352
I would like to throw it away.

01:04:11.559 --> 01:04:16.109
But maybe you can do that instead.

01:04:26.616 --> 01:04:29.736
-Okay.
-Thank you.

01:04:34.290 --> 01:04:36.880
-Let's take a ride.
-Okay.

01:04:53.184 --> 01:04:54.734
Come on.

01:04:58.189 --> 01:05:01.319
Can you believe
he still drives the same stupid truck?

01:05:01.401 --> 01:05:04.701
Sean is a janitor now. He's a real winner.

01:05:04.738 --> 01:05:06.908
-Take the first one?
-No.

01:05:07.532 --> 01:05:08.702
Take it.

01:05:09.117 --> 01:05:10.197
Come on, we're not doing this.

01:05:10.243 --> 01:05:11.333
-Take it!
-This is stupid. No.

01:05:11.411 --> 01:05:14.251
-I'm not doing this. I wanna go back, please.
-Hey, Renee.

01:05:14.330 --> 01:05:17.080
You need this. You don't even understand
how bad you need this.

01:05:17.167 --> 01:05:19.747
I don't need this. I don't need this.
I don't need this.

01:05:19.836 --> 01:05:21.336
He took you from us.
He took you from everything.

01:05:21.379 --> 01:05:22.379
Stop!

01:05:22.464 --> 01:05:24.974
Please, I can't. I can't right now.

01:05:25.050 --> 01:05:29.010
Please. Just forget it. It was a long time ago.

01:06:09.386 --> 01:06:11.216
You don't have to...

01:06:15.517 --> 01:06:17.057
Thank you.

01:06:18.228 --> 01:06:20.058
I've got something for you.

01:06:21.898 --> 01:06:24.068
I got this at three months sober.

01:06:24.150 --> 01:06:26.280
It's your watch thingy.

01:06:26.361 --> 01:06:27.741
Here, look.

01:06:29.406 --> 01:06:31.116
No way.

01:06:33.034 --> 01:06:37.414
"God, grant me the serenity
to accept the things I cannot change,

01:06:37.497 --> 01:06:41.457
"the courage to change the things I can
and the wisdom to know the difference."

01:06:42.836 --> 01:06:44.166
You have to wind it every day.

01:06:44.212 --> 01:06:48.052
It's a little reminder
to take it one day at a time.

01:06:48.091 --> 01:06:50.221
You're like my fairy godmother.

01:06:50.260 --> 01:06:52.350
Did you just call me a fairy?

01:06:52.387 --> 01:06:53.887
Yes.

01:06:59.519 --> 01:07:02.479
Don't say it. Don't say a word.

01:07:04.441 --> 01:07:06.901
-Love you.
-Love you too.

01:07:18.496 --> 01:07:21.076
-How you doing?
-Better.

01:07:21.166 --> 01:07:23.076
Good. Welcome back.

01:10:49.165 --> 01:10:50.705
<i>In our local hero report,</i>

01:10:50.750 --> 01:10:54.590
<i>one young man is making a difference
in the lives of young people in crisis.</i>

01:10:54.671 --> 01:10:58.301
<i>Jamie Tworkowski wrote a story
about a local girl, Renee Yohe,</i>

01:10:58.383 --> 01:11:01.723
<i>who was suffering from addiction,
depression and bipolar disorder</i>

01:11:02.345 --> 01:11:04.845
<i>and got clean with the help of her friends.</i>

01:11:04.889 --> 01:11:08.979
<i>He posted her story on Myspace titled
"To Write Love On Her Arms"</i>

01:11:09.060 --> 01:11:10.600
<i>and it quickly went viral.</i>

01:11:10.687 --> 01:11:12.107
<i>Remembering her scars,</i>

01:11:12.188 --> 01:11:16.528
<i>he printed the unusual logo on T-shirts
to raise money for her treatment.</i>

01:11:16.568 --> 01:11:19.028
<i>Friends in bands
started to wear our T-shirts.</i>

01:11:19.070 --> 01:11:20.990
<i>You know,
they were really generous with their platform.</i>

01:11:21.072 --> 01:11:23.872
<i>Then something crazy
and unexpected happened.</i>

01:11:23.908 --> 01:11:26.198
<i>Thousands of young adults found the page</i>

01:11:26.244 --> 01:11:30.464
<i>and wrote about their own struggles
of depression, addiction and isolation,</i>

01:11:30.540 --> 01:11:35.090
<i>and an online community was born
and became a legitimate social movement.</i>

01:11:35.170 --> 01:11:37.840
<i>Jamie now runs the nonprofit organization</i>

01:11:37.881 --> 01:11:41.471
<i>that is committed to helping others
with similar issues worldwide.</i>

01:11:41.551 --> 01:11:44.721
<i>Renee Yohe has become a role model
for many young people</i>

01:11:44.804 --> 01:11:48.224
<i>and will be speaking at an event
this Friday in Orlando.</i>

01:11:49.351 --> 01:11:52.101
You know, most people are celebrities
before they go into rehab.

01:11:53.063 --> 01:11:55.863
Next week no one will care. Don't worry.

01:11:55.899 --> 01:11:59.399
Well, if this is McKenna's doing,
I'll skin him alive.

01:12:00.403 --> 01:12:01.743
Did you give him this?

01:12:01.821 --> 01:12:05.241
No, no. That's a story he'll have to tell you.

01:12:08.661 --> 01:12:10.001
Oh, boy.

01:12:10.080 --> 01:12:12.620
Yeah? You ready for this?

01:12:14.000 --> 01:12:15.130
I don't know.

01:12:15.210 --> 01:12:16.840
Six months is not a long time.

01:12:17.379 --> 01:12:19.049
Thanks, Doc.

01:12:22.050 --> 01:12:23.300
Hello.

01:12:48.993 --> 01:12:50.753
Renee...

01:12:52.706 --> 01:12:55.206
Sorry, we didn't know
if the surprise was appropriate or anything.

01:12:56.042 --> 01:12:57.502
What's going on?

01:12:57.544 --> 01:12:59.924
-It's like so intense.
-I know.

01:13:00.005 --> 01:13:03.795
I have a manager now
and we're playing some shows

01:13:03.883 --> 01:13:06.053
-and I really want you to come because...
-Shut up. Oh, my God!

01:13:06.803 --> 01:13:08.563
Dylan's a pro.

01:13:08.638 --> 01:13:10.848
Where's McKenna?

01:13:10.890 --> 01:13:12.730
He's taking a break sort of from everything.

01:13:12.767 --> 01:13:13.807
What do you mean?

01:13:13.893 --> 01:13:15.813
His band fired him.

01:13:16.271 --> 01:13:17.401
-No way.
-Yes.

01:13:17.439 --> 01:13:18.729
But he'll be back in a few days.

01:13:18.815 --> 01:13:21.185
-He's just sorting things out.
-Okay.

01:13:21.234 --> 01:13:22.244
Is it my fault?

01:13:22.318 --> 01:13:24.238
-No, no, no.
-'Cause he was babysitting me?

01:13:24.279 --> 01:13:25.279
-No.
-Yeah, it is.

01:13:25.363 --> 01:13:27.623
-No. I would seriously tell you...
-Hi.

01:13:27.699 --> 01:13:29.949
I'm going to go make out with your dad.

01:13:34.414 --> 01:13:37.424
You want some sobriety cake?

01:13:38.376 --> 01:13:40.586
-It's so good.
-Is it?

01:13:40.670 --> 01:13:42.550
This is my second piece,
but I ate the first one in hiding.

01:13:47.385 --> 01:13:48.755
Are you okay?

01:13:49.721 --> 01:13:50.971
Yeah.

01:13:51.681 --> 01:13:53.771
I'm good. It's just a little weird.

01:13:54.100 --> 01:13:55.770
-I know.
-You know what I mean?

01:13:56.978 --> 01:13:58.978
'Cause what are we celebrating, that I'm...

01:13:59.064 --> 01:14:02.034
It's like, "You're normal, yay, party!"

01:14:02.567 --> 01:14:04.437
Well, if you don't want anybody
to be here right now,

01:14:04.527 --> 01:14:05.567
-we can get them out.
-Oh, my God, Jess. Jess.

01:14:05.612 --> 01:14:06.612
Renee!

01:14:07.447 --> 01:14:08.447
Hey!

01:14:09.574 --> 01:14:10.704
Hi!

01:14:10.742 --> 01:14:12.242
I'm so proud of you.

01:14:13.745 --> 01:14:15.365
-Thank you.
-How are you feeling?

01:14:15.413 --> 01:14:18.003
-Much better.
-You look amazing.

01:14:19.876 --> 01:14:23.666
Thanks for all your notes
and sending me letters and all that stuff.

01:14:23.713 --> 01:14:25.053
Of course, of course, of course.

01:14:25.131 --> 01:14:27.131
We have so much to catch up on.

01:14:27.217 --> 01:14:28.337
-It has been a whirlwind!
-I know.

01:14:28.385 --> 01:14:29.465
I want you to come down to the office,

01:14:29.552 --> 01:14:32.972
I want you to see everything that
you've created and what's happened.

01:14:33.765 --> 01:14:34.965
It's beautiful.

01:14:35.058 --> 01:14:36.638
That'd be great, yeah, I'd love to.

01:14:36.726 --> 01:14:38.766
Maybe respond to a few e-mails, yeah?

01:14:39.312 --> 01:14:40.562
Sounds good.

01:14:40.647 --> 01:14:41.767
-Okay?
-Yeah.

01:14:41.898 --> 01:14:44.778
Babe, come meet Renee!

01:14:44.943 --> 01:14:45.993
Hi.

01:14:46.444 --> 01:14:48.664
It's so nice to finally meet you!

01:14:48.738 --> 01:14:51.448
Renee, this is Amanda. She's my girlfriend.

01:14:51.533 --> 01:14:54.083
She's down from New York
for the show on Friday.

01:14:54.160 --> 01:14:56.580
Yeah. Jamie talks about you all the time.

01:14:56.663 --> 01:14:58.463
He's so proud of you.

01:14:58.540 --> 01:15:01.840
And I can't wait for the event on Friday.
It's going to be amazing.

01:15:03.628 --> 01:15:05.878
Are you looking forward to it? Are...

01:15:07.090 --> 01:15:10.720
Well, anyway, it's nice to finally meet you,

01:15:10.760 --> 01:15:13.720
and I can't wait for Friday, and...

01:15:13.763 --> 01:15:14.763
And we've got to catch up.

01:16:34.302 --> 01:16:36.182
-It's like it happened overnight, you know?
-Yeah, yeah.

01:16:36.388 --> 01:16:38.768
We've had this office
for a couple months now.

01:16:39.933 --> 01:16:43.693
In this room we put some of the letters
from, you know, our followers.

01:16:43.728 --> 01:16:44.728
Hey, Renee.

01:16:44.813 --> 01:16:45.813
-Hey.
-Hey, babe.

01:16:45.897 --> 01:16:46.897
That's cool.

01:16:46.940 --> 01:16:48.690
They write to us, you know.
They just want to have a voice.

01:16:48.733 --> 01:16:49.733
Yeah.

